7)
Aside from "ssh-rsa" at the start and the user@host at the end, in id_rsa_homework.pub, I should find the modulus n and the public exponent e according to the specification in RFC 8017 Section A.1.1

To decode the public key, I followed the instructions of The Digital Cat blog post linked in the assignment (https://www.thedigitalcatonline.com/blog/2018/04/25/rsa-keys/).
In my Ubuntu terminal, I typed: cat id_rsa_homework.pub | cut -d " " -f2 | \base64 -d | hexdump -ve '/1 "%02x "' -e '2/8 "\n"'
The 16th - 18th byte is the public exponent and the 23rd byte to the end contains the modulus, according to the blog post
